  "response_text": "The commercial opens on a sunny coastal hillside. The ocean stretches across the right side of the view, with pale surf rolling toward a long beach below. On the left, the slope is thick with spiky plants and coastal shrubs, including large agave-like leaves. A blonde adult woman in a bright yellow-green long-sleeved turtleneck and a patterned golden-brown skirt walks along a narrow path above the shore. She is small at first against the wide landscape, moving through the plants with the cliffs and water behind her.\n\nThe woman is then seen closer, standing among tall pointed succulent leaves with the sea still visible in the background. She has a styled, voluminous blonde bob and a friendly smile. Her outfit includes the fitted green turtleneck, a wide dark belt at her waist, and the warm-toned patterned skirt. She faces forward, presenting herself calmly against the outdoor setting. She raises a black aerosol can beside her shoulder and holds it upright so the front label faces outward. The can is tall and cylindrical, mostly black, with pale horizontal bands and a light circular emblem on the front. As she continues speaking, she keeps the product steady near her face, smiling and occasionally shifting her gaze slightly to the side while the ocean and large spear-shaped leaves fill the background.\n\nThe scene moves indoors to a bathroom or dressing area with a bright window looking out onto leafy plants. The woman now stands near a sink and vanity. A mirror with a decorative wavy frame is on the left above the counter, where small containers sit. Behind her are striped walls, a window with short curtains, and a towel hanging on a rail. She still holds the black Sun Country aerosol can in one hand at chest height. She turns her body slightly toward the window and lifts the can as if to demonstrate it. A pale mist appears in front of the window as she sprays the air freshener, the spray drifting across the bright window area. She then turns back toward the viewer, smiling, with the can still held upright.\n\nA soft transition blends the indoor scene with the coast, and the woman appears outdoors again, seated on the hillside above the ocean. She sits in profile, facing to the right, relaxed with her arms resting on her knees. The same green top and patterned skirt are visible. Around her are low bushes and the open shoreline, with clouds above and calm water beyond. The image emphasizes the fresh outdoor setting.\n\nThe final view returns to the coastal hillside and surf. A large black aerosol can is displayed prominently in the foreground, much bigger than the landscape behind it, standing upright against the ocean view. The label is clear: it shows a white swirling sun-like emblem and the words “SUN COUNTRY” in light lettering on the black can. The product appears centered and dominant, with the beach, waves, cliffs, and spiky plants behind it.",
